# BatiTone ‚Äì Quick Start for Friends  
(works on macOS, Windows, Linux)

## 1. What you need
- Node.js **18 or newer**  
  üëâ [https://nodejs.org](https://nodejs.org) ‚Üê download and run the installer (next-next-finish on both Mac & PC).
- Any terminal (Terminal.app on Mac, PowerShell / CMD on Windows).
- A MongoDB database string (free one is fine ‚Üí [https://www.mongodb.com/atlas](https://www.mongodb.com/atlas) ).

## 2. Zip / folder
- Keep **all files** exactly as you got them (especially `package.json`, `server.js`, `.env.example`, `uploads` folder, etc.).

## 3. One-time setup
1. Open terminal **inside the BatiTone folder** (drag the folder onto the terminal icon Mac, or Shift-right-click ‚Üí ‚ÄúOpen PowerShell window here‚Äù Windows).
2. Install dependencies:  
   ```bash
   npm install
   ```
3. Copy the example environment:  
   Mac / Linux:
   ```bash
   cp .env.example .env
   ```
   Windows (PowerShell):
   ```powershell
   Copy-Item .env.example .env
   ```
4. Edit `.env` with any text editor:
   ```
   MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://<user>:<password>@cluster0.xxxxx.mongodb.net/batiTone
   JWT_SECRET=any-phrase-you-like
   ```
   Save and close.

## 4. Run the server
Same terminal:
```bash
npm run dev
```
Wait for:  
`http://localhost:3000` ‚Üê open this in Chrome / Safari / Edge.  
That‚Äôs it ‚Äî the site is live on your own laptop.

## 5. Stop
Press `Ctrl + C` (Mac & Windows) in the terminal to shut it down.


## 6. How to use BatiTone (once the server is running)

1. **Open the site**  
   Go to [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) in Chrome, Safari, or Edge.

2. **Create an account**  
   Click ‚ÄúSign Up,‚Äù pick Student or Teacher, fill in your name / email / password, then ‚ÄúRegister.‚Äù  
   (Teachers get a class-code maker; students get a code box.)

3. **Student path ‚Äì quick ear-training**  
   - Log in ‚Üí **Practice** ‚Üí choose **Notes, Intervals, Melody, Chords,** or **Rhythm**.  
   - Hit the big green **Start** button.  
   - Listen, then:  
     ‚Äì *Sing* into your laptop mic, **or**  
     ‚Äì *Tap* the on-screen piano, **or**  
     ‚Äì *Plug in a USB MIDI keyboard* and play.  
   - instant green = correct, red = try again.  
   - After 7 short questions your score appears and the site auto-levels you up or down.

4. **Score practice (optional)**  
   - Click **Score Practice** ‚Üí drag any **.xml / .mxl / .mid** file into the box.  
   - The sheet music appears; press **Play**.  
   - Click any two bars to **loop** them, drag the **tempo** slider to slow it down, or **mute** one hand so you can play it yourself.

5. **Teacher path**  
   - Log in ‚Üí **Create Class** ‚Üí copy the 6-letter code.  
   - Give the code to students; they type it once and they‚Äôre enrolled.  
   - Open **Dashboard** ‚Üí green bars = good, red bars = needs help.  
   - Hit **Export CSV** to download a ready-made grade-book.

6. **Tiny tips**  
   - Green loop bars = repeat section; count-in = gives you a one-bar warning.  
   - Needle gauge = tuner for singing; flashes green + ‚Äúding‚Äù when you‚Äôre spot-on.  
   - Works offline after first visit (cached sounds), but scores need Wi-Fi to save.

Enjoy training your ears!